Preheat the oven to 210°C. In a #bowl{}, combine the @tandoori masala spice{1}, @tomato puree{30%g} and half the @low fat natural yoghurt{75%g}. Season with @salt{}, @pepper{} and a pinch of @sugar{for the pickle}. Add the @diced chicken breast{260%g} and stir to combine. Set aside.

> IMPORTANT: Remember to wash your hands after handling raw meat.

Halve, peel and thinly slice the @red onion{1/2}. Pop in a bowl with the @cider vinegar{15%g}, sugar and half the @nigella seeds{1}. Season with salt and pepper, stir well and set aside.

Chop the @tomato{2%medium} into 2cm chunks. Trim the @cucumber{1/2} then halve lengthways. Chop each half into 4 long strips then chop widthways into small pieces. Pick the @mint{1/2}(leaves picked from stalks) and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Roughly chop the @coriander{1}(stalks and all). Trim the root from the @iceberg lettuce{1/2} then half lengthways. Thinly slice widthways.

Pop the tomatoes in a bowl with the remaining nigella seeds and half the coriander. Add a drizzle of @oil{} and a pinch of @salt{} and pepper. Toss to combine and set aside. In another bowl, combine the cucumber, remaining yoghurt and half the mint. Set aside.

Pop the @sweet potato fries{250%g} on a #baking tray{}, drizzle with @oil{}, season with @salt{} and pepper. Toss to coat. Spread out and roast on the middle shelf of the oven until soft and golden, ~{18-20%minutes}.

Line a baking tray with #foil{}. Put the marinated chicken on the tray and bake on the top shelf until cooked through, ~{10-12%minutes}, turning halfway.

> TIP: Don't be afraid if the chicken chars - this will add to the flavour!

Pop the @plain naans{2} directly on the oven shelf to warm through for the final ~{1-2%minutes}. Get ready to serve.

This dish is all about piling it high! Put a naan on each #plate{} and top with the lettuce, followed by the tandoori chicken, sweet potato fries, tomato salad and cucumber raita. Scatter the pickled onions over the top, followed by a drizzle of @sweet chilli sauce{32%g}. Finish with the remaining chopped coriander and mint and dig in!